    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Zen Buddhism, satori refers to a sudden personal enlightenment analagous to the original moment of spiritual rebirth experienced by the Gautama Buddha.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
